OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30202
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773435971
OL,3,CMPs criticise Fujitsu for not
OL,4,Ccontributing 'a penny' to Post Office
OL,5,Credress
OL,7,FMore than 11,500 claimants have
OL,8,Freceived payments worth approximately
OL,9,F#1.48 billion, as of February 27,
OL,10,Fthrough several schemes set up to
OL,11,Fcompensate postmasters who were
OL,12,Faffected by previous faulty versions
OL,13,Fof the Horizon computer system.
OL,15,FThe total costs of redress rise to
OL,16,Faround #2 billion once legal and
OL,17,Fadministrative costs are taken into
OL,18,Faccount, as well as for the Capture
OL,19,Fsystem which pre-dates the Horizon
OL,20,Fsoftware.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30203
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773435971
OL,3,CMPs criticise Fujitsu for not
OL,4,Ccontributing 'a penny' to Post Office
OL,5,Credress
OL,7,FThe Horizon accounting system, run by
OL,8,FJapanese firm Fujitsu, made it look
OL,9,Flike money was missing from their
OL,10,Fbranch accounts.
OL,12,FIt is at the centre of the long-
OL,13,Frunning Post Office scandal, which saw
OL,14,Faround 1,000 people wrongly prosecuted
OL,15,Fand convicted throughout the UK
OL,16,Fbetween 1999 and 2015.
OL,18,FThe BTC said progress had been made in
OL,19,Fdelivering redress to victims, but
OL,20,Fthat thousands of sub-postmasters were
OL,21,Fstill waiting for compensation.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30204
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773435971
OL,3,CMPs criticise Fujitsu for not
OL,4,Ccontributing 'a penny' to Post Office
OL,5,Credress
OL,7,FMany victims still face delays,
OL,8,Finadequate offers, and administrative
OL,9,Fprocesses that "retraumatise" those
OL,10,Fwho have already faced injustice,
OL,11,Faccording to its report.
OL,13,FMP Liam Byrne, chairman of the BTC,
OL,14,Fsaid: "Thousands of victims are still
OL,15,Fwaiting for fair redress, while the
OL,16,Fprocesses designed to help them are
OL,17,Ftoo often slow, bureaucratic and
OL,18,Fretraumatising.
OL,26,@qD@POUqD@]O]vD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30205
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773435971
OL,3,CMPs criticise Fujitsu for not
OL,4,Ccontributing 'a penny' to Post Office
OL,5,Credress
OL,7,F"That is simply unacceptable after one
OL,8,Fof the greatest miscarriages of
OL,9,Fjustice in British history.
OL,11,F"Worse, Fujitsu has yet to contribute
OL,12,Fa penny to the nearly #2 billion
OL,13,Fredress bill, even as it continues to
OL,14,Fbenefit from public contracts."
OL,16,FHe added: "It is simply wrong that
OL,17,Ftaxpayers are covering the costs for
OL,18,FFujitsu's sins while Fujitsu is still
OL,19,Fprofiting from taxpayers-funded
OL,20,Fcontracts."
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOUxD@KOU|D@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,303,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30206
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F302A1773435971
OL,3,CMPs criticise Fujitsu for not
OL,4,Ccontributing 'a penny' to Post Office
OL,5,Credress
OL,7,FThe BTC said that Fujitsu had
OL,8,Facknowledged it had a "moral
OL,9,Fobligation" to contribute to the cost
OL,10,Fof redress, and stated its commitment
OL,11,Fto do so, but that it has made no
OL,12,Finterim payment nor agreed to any
OL,13,Ffigure.
OL,15,FFujitsu continues to supply its IT
OL,16,Fsystem to the Post Office and also to
OL,17,Fgovernment departments through a
OL,18,Fnumber of contracts.
OL,26,@pD@WOUqD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
